sVnews
p4
VOn the third day of the music festival jointly organised by Sri Sadguru Sangeeta Sabha and G.V.R. Government College of Music and Dance, Vijayawada , B. Saraswathi, a well known singer and a staff artiste of Vijayawada Akashvani, gave a pleasing concert. Saraswathi sports a felicitous and mellow voice. She sang in pure traditional style that pleased connoisseurs. Saraswathi began the concert with Natakuranji varnam following it with a rare keertana Gopalaka Pahimam Anisam in Bowli finishing it with fine kalpana swaras. After rendering Ganamurthe in the third Melakarta raga Ganamurthi, she presented a pleasing delineation of Sahana and sang Eevasudha Neevanti Daivamu with appealing bhava.Saraswathi gave her best in the main item Ninne Namminanu in Todi. A beautiful portrait of the rage was hoisted by her and the kalpana swaras were of high professional order. She got excellent support on violin by B.V. Durga Bhavani, B.V.S. Prasad on mridangam and S. Hanumanta Rao on ghatam. Durga Bhavani played a melodious version of Todi and the percussion team presented a thrilling tani. Saraswathi closed the concert with a Devaranama.
